1 (2) Effective July 1, 1995, every state agency which is a
2 participating employer shall contribute to the System an amount
3 equal to eleven and one-half percent (11 1/2%) of the monthly
4 compensation of each member, not to exceed the allowable annual
5 compensation as defined in paragraph (9) of Section 902 of this
6 title.
7 (3) Effective July 1, 1996, every state agency which is a
8 participating employer shall contribute to the System an amount
9 equal to twelve percent (12%) of the monthly compensation of each
10 member, not to exceed the allowable annual compensation defined in
11 paragraph (9) of Section 902 of this title.
12 (4) Effective July 1, 1999, and through the fiscal year ending
13 June 30, 2005, every state agency which is a participating employer
14 shall contribute to the System an amount equal to ten percent (10%)
15 of the monthly compensation of each member, not to exceed the
16 allowable annual compensation defined in paragraph (9) of Section
17 902 of this title.
18 (5) Effective July 1, 2005, except as otherwise provided by
19 subsection (11) (13) of this section, every state agency which is a
20 participating employer shall contribute an amount to the System
21 equal to a percentage of monthly compensation of each member, not to
22 exceed the allowable annual compensation defined in paragraph (9) of
23 Section 902 of this title as follows:
24 July 1, 2005 – June 30, 2006 11 1/2%
