7 (6) Beginning July 1, 2026, through June 30, 2031, except as
8 otherwise provided by subsection (13) of this section, every state
9 agency which is a participating employer shall contribute an amount
10 to the System equal to nine and one-half percent (9 1/2%) of monthly
11 compensation of each member, not to exceed the allowable annual
12 compensation defined in paragraph (9) of Section 902 of this title.
13 (7) Beginning July 1, 2031, except as otherwise provided by
14 subsection (13) of this section, every state agency which is a
15 participating employer shall contribute an amount to the System
16 equal to sixteen and one-half percent (16 1/2%) of monthly
17 compensation of each member, not to exceed the allowable annual
18 compensation defined in paragraph (9) of Section 902 of this title.
19 (8) The Board shall certify, on or before November 1 of each
20 year, to the Office of Management and Enterprise Services an
21 actuarially determined estimate of the rate of contribution which
22 will be required, together with all accumulated contributions and
23 other assets of the System, to be paid by each participating
24 employer to pay all liabilities which shall exist or accrue under
