1 the System, including amortization of the past service cost over a
2 period of not to exceed forty (40) years from June 30, 1987, and the
3 cost of administration of the System, as determined by the Board,
4 upon recommendation of the actuary.
5 (7) (9) The Office of Management and Enterprise Services and
6 the Governor shall include in the budget and in the budget request
7 for appropriations the sum required to satisfy the state's
8 obligation under this section as certified by the Board and shall
9 present the same to the Legislature for allowance and appropriation.
10 (8) (10) Each other participating employer shall appropriate
11 and pay to the System a sum sufficient to satisfy the obligation
12 under this section as certified by the Board.
13 (9) (11) Each participating employer is hereby authorized to
14 pay the employer's contribution from the same fund that the
15 compensation for which said contribution is paid from or from any
16 other funds available to it for such purpose.
17 (10) (12) Forfeitures arising from severance of employment,
18 death or for any other reason may not be applied to increase the
19 benefits any member would otherwise receive under the System's law.
20 However, forfeitures may be used to reduce an employer's
21 contribution.
22 (11) (13) Effective November 1, 2015, an employer shall be
23 required to make payment to the Oklahoma Public Employees Retirement
24 System of the amount described by subsection A of Section 10 of this
