1 act 935.10 of this title with respect to any employee who is a
2 participant in the defined contribution system created pursuant to
3 the provisions of Sections 1 935.1 through 11 935.11 of this act
4 title. The employer shall be required to make the required matching
5 contribution amount for all employees that participate in the
6 defined contribution system and to remit the difference between such
7 amount and the amount the employer would otherwise have paid
8 pursuant to the provisions of this section to the Oklahoma Public
9 Employees Retirement System.
10 SECTION 2. This act shall become effective July 1, 2026.
11 SECTION 3. It being immediately necessary for the preservation
12 of the public peace, health or safety, an emergency is hereby
13 declared to exist, by reason whereof this act shall take effect and
14 be in full force from and after its passage and approval.
